rathon]] race held in [[Berlin]], [[Germany]], held on 25 September 1994. Portugal's [[Ant\u00f3nio Pinto (runner)|Ant\u00f3nio Pinto]] won the men's race in 2:08:31&nbsp;hours, while the women's race was won by home athlete [[Katrin D\u00f6rre-Heinig]] in 2:25:15.<ref>[http://more.arrs.run/race/44571 Results]. [[Association of Road Racing Statisticians]]. Retrieved 2020-04-02.</ref>\n\n== Results ==\n=== Men ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Position \n! Athlete \n! Nationality\n! Time\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}1 \n| [[Ant\u00f3nio Pinto (runner)|Ant\u00f3nio Pinto]]\n| {{POR}}\n| 2:08:31\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}2 \n| [[Sam Nyangincha]]\n| {{KEN}}\n| 2:08:50\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}3 \n| [[Antonio Serrano]]\n| {{ESP}}\n| 2:09:13\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}4 \n| [[Lameck Aguta]]\n| {{KEN}}\n| 2:10:41\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}5 \n| [[Bert van Vlaanderen]]\n| {{NED}}\n| 2:10:49\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}6 \n| [[Jackson Kipngok]]\n| {{KEN}}\n| 2:12:12\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}7 \n| [[Gilbert Rutto]]\n| {{KEN}}\n| 2:12:36\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}8 \n| [[Juvenal Ribeiro]]\n| {{POR}}\n| 2:12:52\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}9 \n| [[Samson Maritim]]\n| {{KEN}}\n| 2:12:59\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| 10\n| [[Miros\u0142aw Plawgo]]\n| {{POL}}\n| 2:13:05\n|}\n\n=== Women ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Position \n! Athlete \n! Nationality\n! Time\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}1 \n| [[Katrin D\u00f6rre-Heinig]]\n| {{GER}}\n| 2:25:15\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}2 \n| [[Roc\u00edo R\u00edos]]\n| {{ESP}}\n| 2:29:00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}3 \n| [[Ma\u0142gorzata Soba\u0144ska]]\n| {{POL}}\n| 2:30:00\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}4 \n| [[Kirsi Mattila]]\n| {{FIN}}\n| 2:31:23\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"| {{0}}5 \n| [[Sonja Oberem]]\n| {{GER}}\n| 2:31:35\n|-\n| style=\