{"title_page": "Alison Brie", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Alison Brie\n| image              = Alison Brie by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Brie at the 2012 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_name         = Alison Brie Schermerhorn\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1982|12|29}}\n| birth_place        = [[Hollywood]], [[California]], U.S.\n| occupation         = Actress\n| known for          = ''[[Mad Men]]'' (2007-2015), \n\n''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]'' (2009-2015) <br/> ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' (2014-2020) <br/> ''[[GLOW (TV series)|GLOW]]'' (2017-present)\n| alma_mater         = [[California Institute of the Arts]]\n| years_active       = 2004\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{Marriage|[[Dave Franco]]|2017}}\n}}\n\n'''Alison Brie Schermerhorn''' (born December 29, 1982) is an American actress. Brie is best known for her starring roles as [[Annie Edison]] in the comedy series ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]'' (2009\u20132015), [[Trudy Campbell]] in the drama series ''[[Mad Men]]'' (2007\u20132015), [[Diane Nguyen]] in the animated comedy series ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'' (2014\u20132020) and as Ruth Wilder in the comedy-drama series ''[[GLOW (TV series)|GLOW]]'' (2017\u2013present), for which she received nominations for the [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series|Screen Actors Guild Award]] and the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy]].\n\nIn addition to her television work, Brie has starred in films such as ''[[Scream 4]]'' (2011), ''[[The Five-Year Engagement]]'' (2012), ''[[The Lego Movie]]'' (2014), ''[[Get Hard]]'' (2015), ''[[Sleeping with Other People]]'' (2015), ''[[How to Be Single]]'' (2016), ''[[The Little Hours]]'' (2017), ''[[The Disaster Artist (film)|The Disaster Artist]]'' (2017), ''[[The Post (film)|The Post]]'' (2017), ''[[Promising Young Woman]]'' (2020), and ''[[Horse Girl]]'' (2020), the lattermost of which she also co-wrote and produced.\n\n==Early life==\nAlison Brie Schermerhorn was born on December 29, 1982,<!--- 1982 is correct ---> in [[Hollywood]], [[California]].<ref>{{cite interview|first=Alison|last=Brie|interviewer=Marc Maron|url=http://www.wtfpod.com/podcast/episodes/episode_386_-_alison_brie|title=Episode 386 - Alison Brie|website=WTFPod.com|date=May 8, 2013|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Robertson|first1=Josh|title=25 Things You Didn't Know About Alison Brie|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2013/02/25-things-you-didnt-know-about-alison-brie/alison-brie-clown-named-sunny|accessdate=June 28, 2017|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=February 26, 2013|language=en}}</ref> Her father, Charles Terry Schermerhorn, is a musician and freelance entertainment reporter.<ref name=\"HC wedding\">{{cite web|url=https://lwpolive.heraldchronicle.com/olive/ode/winchester/LandingPage/LandingPage.aspx?href=TFdDLzIwMTAvMTEvMjY.&pageno=MTI.&entity=QXIwMTIwMQ..&view=ZW50aXR5|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20140420011759/http://lwpolive.heraldchronicle.com/olive/ode/winchester/LandingPage/LandingPage.aspx?href=TFdDLzIwMTAvMTEvMjY.&pageno=MTI.&entity=QXIwMTIwMQ..&view=ZW50aXR5|url-status=dead|archive-date=April 20, 2014|title=Schermerhorn, Brandenstein Wed In Summer Ceremony|website=HeraldChronicle.com}}</ref><ref name=PWeekly>{{cite news|url=http://www.pasadenaweekly.com/cms/story/detail/a_shooting_star/7555|title=A Shooting star Alison Brie is one of the busiest young actresses in Hollywood...|date=August 1, 2009|website=[[Pasadena Weekly]]|first=Carl|last=Kozlowski|accessdate=January 17, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204155048/http://www.pasadenaweekly.com/cms/story/detail/a_shooting_star/7555/|archive-date=February 4, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> Her mother, Joanne Brenner, works at Para los Ni\u00f1os (\"For the Children\"), a non-profit childcare agency.<ref>[http://www.cmfa-ca.com/resources/CMFA%20Board%20Package%201%2011%2013.pdf Staff Reports] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140430060714/http://www.cmfa-ca.com/resources/CMFA%20Board%20Package%201%2011%2013.pdf |date=April 30, 2014}}, California Municipal Finance Authority</ref> She has an older sister named Lauren.<ref name=\"HC wedding\"/><ref name=PWeekly/> Brie's mother is [[Jewish]].<ref name=very>{{cite web|url=http://www.jta.org/2013/05/09/arts-entertainment/alison-brie-talks-jewish-mother-drama-on-wtf-with-marc-maron|title=Alison Brie on her very Jewish mother|website=[[Jewish Telegraphic Agency]]|date=May 9, 2013|first=Jana|last=Banin|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Sam|last=Fragoso|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/sundance-film-festival-alison-brie-nudity|title=At Sundance, Alison Brie Steers the Conversation Back to Nudity|work=Vogue magazine|date=January 27, 2017|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Brendan|last=Morrow|url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/06/alison-brie-family-mother-father-parents-sister-lauren-dave-franco/|title=Alison Brie's Family: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|work=[[Heavy.com]]|date=June 23, 2017|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Kaleem|last=Aftab|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/alison-brie-on-sleeping-with-other-people-mad-men-and-being-a-very-serious-actress-a6788606.html|title=Alison Brie on 'Sleeping with Other People', 'Mad Men', and being a very serious actress|work=[[The Independent]]|date=December 28, 2015|accessdate=May 13, 2018}}</ref> Her father has Dutch, English, and Scottish ancestry. While being raised by her divorced parents, she occasionally attended a \"[[Christianity|Christian]]\u2013[[Hindu]] hybrid church\" called the [[Self-Realization Fellowship]] with her father. However, her mother \"would always make sure we knew we were [[Jewish]]\".<ref name=very /><ref name=dp30>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orKphoKU3Ck|title=DP/30 Emmywatch: Community/Mad Men, actor Alison Brie|website=Emmywatch}}</ref><ref name=\"popmatters\">{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/pm/feature/116229-alison-brie-and-donald-glover-of-community|title=Alison Brie and Donald Glover of 'Community'|date=November 17, 2009|website=PopMatters.com|accessdate=November 17, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091120041134/http://www.popmatters.com/pm/feature/116229-alison-brie-and-donald-glover-of-community|archivedate=November 20, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBrie began acting onstage at the [[Jewish Community Center]] in [[Southern California]].<ref name=PWeekly /><ref name=\"slant\">{{cite web|last=Andelman|first=Bob|title=From Mad Men's Trudy to Community's Annie, actor Alison Brie is a hit|website=True/Slant|date=November 12, 2009|url=http://trueslant.com/bobandelman/2009/11/12/from-mad-mens-trudy-to-communitys-annie-actor-alison-brie-is-a-hit/|accessdate=November 18, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724074930/http://trueslant.com/bobandelman/2009/11/12/from-mad-mens-trudy-to-communitys-annie-actor-alison-brie-is-a-hit/|archive-date=July 24, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref> She graduated from the [[California Institute of the Arts]] with a [[bachelor's degree]] in theater in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lippsisters.com/2008/10/12/exclusive-alison-brie-interview-part-1-and-toto-too|title=Exclusive Alison Brie Interview, part 1|last=Lipp|first=Deborah|date=October 12, 2008|website=Basket of Kisses|accessdate=September 18, 2009}}</ref> She also lived in [[Scotland]], where she studied at the [[Royal Conservatoire of Scotland|Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama]] in [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]].<ref name=PWeekly/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RF_OzYINplo|title=Alison Brie on The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson|website=YouTube|date=October 29, 2010|accessdate=September 30, 2009}}</ref> She later worked as a clown at birthday parties and performed in theater in California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esquire.com/women/funny-joke-from-a-beautiful-woman/alison-brie-photo-1009|title=Alison Brie: Funny Joke from a Beautiful Woman|last=Price|first=Erik|date=September 11, 2009|website=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]|accessdate=September 18, 2009|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090915172243/http://www.esquire.com/women/funny-joke-from-a-beautiful-woman/alison-brie-photo-1009|archivedate=September 15, 2009|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Alison Brie.jpg|thumb|Brie at the 2009 [[LA Film Festival]]]]\n\nOne of Brie's first television roles was as Nina, a novice [[hairdresser]], on the [[Disney Channel]] sitcom ''[[Hannah Montana]]''. She went on to star in the web series ''[[My Alibi]]'', and was chosen for the role of [[Trudy Campbell]] in the period drama series ''[[Mad Men]]''. From 2009 to 2015, she portrayed [[Annie Edison]] on the [[NBC]] (and later [[Yahoo! View]]) sitcom ''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]''.\n\nIn April 2010, Brie co-hosted an episode of ''[[Attack of the Show!]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Alison Brie on Attack of the Show [2011-04-14]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0lwSAcXqhwc|website=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=May 7, 2013}}</ref> and appeared in a segment on ''[[Web Soup]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Web Soup: Alison Brie Laughs at Dead People|url=http://www.bing.com/videos/watch/video/alison-brie-laughs-at-dead-people/17wt3po4l?cpkey=0b188051-60ed-4b7a-a0b4-725002533344%257c%257c%257c%257c|website=Bing|accessdate=May 7, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014151012/http://www.bing.com/videos/watch/video/alison-brie-laughs-at-dead-people/17wt3po4l?cpkey=0b188051-60ed-4b7a-a0b4-725002533344%7C%7C%7C%7C|archive-date=October 14, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> She appeared in the 2010 comedy film ''[[The Misadventures of the Dunderheads|Montana Amazon]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinematical.com/2008/04/07/casting-bites-part-two-some-brie-and-strik/|title=Casting Bites, Part Two: Some Brie and Strik|last=Bartyzel|first=Monika|date=April 7, 2008|website=Cinematical|accessdate=September 18, 2009}}</ref> Brie made [[Maxim (magazine)|''Maxim'' magazine]]'s 2010 Hot 100 list at number 99<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxim.com/girls/girls-of-maxim/92660/2010-hot-100.html#2|title=2010 Hot 100|website=Maxim|accessdate=May 26, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100526173533/http://www.maxim.com/girls/girls-of-maxim/92660/2010-hot-100.html|archivedate=May 26, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref> and appeared at number 49 in their 2011 list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maxim.com/amg/GIRLS/Articles/2011+Hot+100 |title=2011 Hot 100 |website=Maxim |accessdate=May 3, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609204706/http://www.maxim.com/amg/GIRLS/Articles/2011%2BHot%2B100 |archivedate=June 9, 2011 |url-status=dead}}</ref> She was voted the [[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|57th Sexiest Woman in the World]] by ''[[FHM]]'' readers in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/alison-brie|title=Alison Brie|website=FHM|accessdate=June 28, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508121220/http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/alison-brie|archive-date=May 8, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> She was also voted the 2nd most desirable woman in the world by [[AskMen]] readers in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldenow.com/2014/02/emilia-clarke-tops-askmens-women-2014-list/ |title=Emilia Clarke Voted Most Desirable Woman |accessdate=March 5, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306054124/http://worldenow.com/2014/02/emilia-clarke-tops-askmens-women-2014-list/ |archivedate=March 6, 2014}}</ref>\n\nBrie starred in several major film roles, including [[Sidney Prescott]]'s assistant in the 2011 horror film ''[[Scream 4]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/20770|title='Community' Chick and 'Donnie Darko' Mom Join 'Scream' Mystery|website=[[Bloody Disgusting]]|date=July 1, 2010|accessdate=August 21, 2011|last=Miska|first=Brad}}</ref> and appeared in the 2012 comedy film ''[[The Five-Year Engagement]]''. She voiced Princess Unikitty in ''[[The Lego Movie]]'' (2014), and voiced a character in an episode of the animated series ''[[American Dad!]]'', which aired during their [[American Dad! (season 8)|eighth season]].<ref name=\"variety1\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/tv/news/kim-kardashian-to-play-alien-on-american-dad-1200665746/|title=Kim Kardashian 'American Dad'; Reality Star to Play Alien on Comedy|website=Variety|accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"insidetv1\">{{cite web|last=Hibberd|first=James|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2013/09/24/american-dad-kim-kardashian/|title=Kim Kardashian to play alien on 'American Dad'|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, Brie joined the cast of the [[Netflix]] series ''[[BoJack Horseman]]'', which debuted on August 22. Over the first two seasons, she has voiced a variety of characters, including main character [[Diane Nguyen]] and recurring character Vincent Adultman.<ref>{{cite web|last=Knight|first=James|title='Mad Men' Alison Brie New Netflix Show Bojack with 'Breaking Bad' Aaron Paul After 'Community' Cancellation [TRAILER]|url=http://www.classicalite.com/articles/8893/20140607/mad-men-alison-brie-new-netflix-show-bojack-breaking-bad.htm|website=Classicalite.com|accessdate=June 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Strecker|first=Erin|title='BoJack Horseman': New Netflix comedy features voices of Will Arnett, Amy Sedaris, more|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2014/06/04/bojack-horseman-netflix-will-arnett/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=June 17, 2014|date=April 6, 2014}}</ref> Brie also appeared on ''[[Lip Sync Battle]]'' and won against [[Will Arnett]] with performances of \"[[Shoop (song)|Shoop]]\" by [[Salt-N-Pepa]] and \"[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]\" by [[Jessie J]], [[Ariana Grande]], and [[Nicki Minaj]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spike.com/episodes/77pjpt/lip-sync-battle-alison-brie-vs-will-arnett-season-1-ep-117|title=Alison Brie beats Will Arnett on Lip Sync Battle|website=Spike.com}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she starred with [[Jason Sudeikis]] in [[Leslye Headland]]'s romantic comedy film ''[[Sleeping with Other People]]'', and played [[Will Ferrell]]'s character's fianc\u00e9e in the comedy film ''[[Get Hard]]''.<ref name=\"Alison\">{{cite web|last=Fleming Jr|first=Mike|title='Community's Alison Brie Joins Will Ferrell-Kevin Hart Comedy 'Get Hard'|url=https://deadline.com/2014/03/communitys-alison-brie-joins-will-ferrell-kevin-hart-comedy-get-hard/|accessdate=March 18, 2014|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 17, 2014}}</ref> In 2016, Brie starred as Lucy in the romantic comedy film ''[[How to Be Single]]''. In 2017, she co-starred in several films, including the historical comedy ''[[The Little Hours]]'', the biographical comedy-drama ''[[The Disaster Artist (film)|The Disaster Artist]]'', and the historical drama ''[[The Post (film)|The Post]]''.\n\nIn 2017, Brie began her starring role as Ruth Wilder in the Netflix comedy-drama series ''[[GLOW (TV series)|GLOW]]'', inspired by the 1980s female professional wrestling promotion [[Gorgeous Ladies of Wrestling]];<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=August 29, 2016|title=Alison Brie To Star In Netflix Comedy Series 'G.L.O.W.' From Jenji Kohan|url=https://deadline.com/2016/08/alison-brie-star-glow-netflix-wrestling-comedy-series-jenji-kohan-1201810007/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=October 21, 2016}}</ref> the series began streaming on June 23, 2017. Brie noted that since appearing in ''GLOW'' and receiving critical praise for the role, she has become more focused on taking meaningful roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/alison-brie-talks-finding-meaningful-projects-glow-i-became-very-picky-1071573|title=Alison Brie Talks Finding \"Meaningful\" Projects: \"After 'GLOW,' I Became Very Picky\"|date=January 8, 2018|first=Mia|last=Galuppo|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, she co-starred in the music video for [[Beck]]'s \"Colors\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Leight|first=Ellias|date=March 29, 2018|title=See Beck Dance With Alison Brie in Vivid 'Colors' Video|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/see-beck-dance-with-alison-brie-in-vivid-colors-video-629943/|website=[[RollingStone]]|accessdate=January 4, 2019}}</ref> In 2019, she reprised her voice role as Princess Unikitty in the animated comedy sequel film ''[[The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part]]'' and provided an English dub for the Japanese animated romantic fantasy film ''[[Weathering with You]]''.\n\nIn 2020, Brie starred in the acclaimed drama thriller film ''[[Promising Young Woman]]'', directed by [[Emerald Fennell]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/bo-burnham-alison-brie-connie-britton-adam-brody-carey-mulligan-promising-young-woman-cast-1202585238/|title=Bo Burnham To Star Opposite Carey Mulligan In 'Promising Young Woman'; Alison Brie, Connie Britton, Adam Brody & More Round Cast|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}</ref> Also in 2020, she wrote, produced and starred as Sarah in the Netflix drama film ''[[Horse Girl]]'', which was directed by [[Jeff Baena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/horse-girl-netflix-movie-cast-character-guide/|title=Netflix's Horse Girl Cast & Character Guide|last=Hough|first=Quinn|work=Screenrant|date=February 7, 2020|access-date=February 7, 2020}}</ref> Brie will next star opposite [[Dan Stevens]] in the horror film ''[[The Rental]]'', which was directed by husband Dave Franco.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/dave-franco-directing-debut-the-rental-alison-brie-dan-stevens-black-bear-pictures-1202573418/|title=Alison Brie, Dan Stevens To Star In Dave Franco Directing Debut 'The Rental'|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Mike|last=Fleming Jr|date=March 11, 2019|accessdate=April 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBrie began dating [[Dave Franco]] in 2012 after meeting him at a 2011 [[Mardi Gras]] party in [[New Orleans]].<ref name=\"EOnline Engaged\">{{cite web|first=Marc|last=Malkin|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/689488/exclusive-alison-brie-and-dave-franco-engaged-see-the-ring-now|title=Exclusive! Alison Brie and Dave Franco Engaged\u2014See the Ring Now|date=August 24, 2015|website=E! Online|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> On August 25, 2015, it was reported the two were engaged.<ref name=\"EOnline Engaged\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/dave-franco-alison-brie-engaged|title=Alison Brie and Dave Franco Are Engaged!|first=Char|last=Adams|date=August 25, 2015|website=[[People (magazine)|People]].com|accessdate=January 17, 2016}}</ref> They married on March 13, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etonline.com/news/212833_dave_franco_and_alison_brie_are_married/|title=Dave Franco and Alison Brie Are Married!|date=March 13, 2017|accessdate=April 19, 2017|website=[[ET Online]]|first=Meredith|last=Kile}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Stolen Poem''\n| Alice\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2007\n| ''Born''\n| Mary Elizabeth Martino\n|\n|-\n| ''Dickie Smalls: From Shame to Fame''\n| Mya\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2008\n| ''[[Parasomnia (film)|Parasomnia]]''\n| Darcy\n|\n|-\n| ''{{sortname|The|Coverup}}''\n| Grace\n|\n|-\n| ''Buddy 'n' Andy''\n| Michelle\n| rowspan=\"4\" | Short film\n|-\n| ''Salvation, Texas''\n| Lisa Salter\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Us One Night''\n| Alyson\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2010\n| ''{{sortname|The|Home Front|nolink=1}}''\n| Hannah\n|-\n| ''[[Raspberry Magic]]''\n| Ms. Bradlee\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Scream 4]]''\n| Reb