k=IGN|accessdate=February 28, 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Web===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2008\u20132009\n| ''[[My Alibi]]''\n| Rebecca Fuller\n| 18 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Hot Sluts''\n| Amber<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comedycentral.com/cc-studios/hot-sluts|title=Alison Brie falls in with the wrongest crowd possible|publisher=Comedy Central}}</ref>\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''Sketchy''\n| Meg\n| Episode: \"You Got Retweeted\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''{{sortname|The|ArScheerio Paul Show|nolink=1}}''\n| [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]\n| Episode: \"Madonna & [[Rosie O'Donnell]]\"\n|}\n\n=== Music videos ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Artist\n! Role\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"Colors\"\n| [[Beck]]\n| Herself\n|\n|}\n\n===Theme Park attraction===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Lego Movie: 4D - A New Adventure]]''\n| Princess Unikitty (voice)\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Drama Series]]\n|''[[Mad Men]]''\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Critics' Choice Television Award]]s\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series|Best Supporting Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n|''[[Community (TV series)|Community]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"| 2018\n| [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actress in a Comedy Series|Best Actress in a Comedy Series]]\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''[[GLOW (TV series)|GLOW]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Satellite Awards]]\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy|Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Golden Globe Awards]]\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy|Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Musical or Comedy]]\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite journal |last=Smith |first=Nigel |title=First-Time Winner Rachel Brosnahan Pauses Globes Acceptance Speech for a Good Reason: 'Hi, Oprah!' |url=http://people.com/tv/golden-globes-2018-best-comedy-actress-rachel-brosnahan/ |date=January 8, 2018 |accessdate=January 8, 2018 |journal=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Plaugic |first=Lizzie |title=Rachel Brosnahan wins 2018's Best Actress Golden Globe for Amazon's ''The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel'' |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/1/7/16861572/golden-globes-2018-rachel-brosnahan-the-marvelous-mrs-maisel-win |date=January 8, 2018 |accessdate=January 8, 2018 |journal=[[The Verge]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Otterson |first=Joe |title=''Mrs. Maisel'' Star Rachel Brosnahan Advocates for More Women's Stories During Golden Globes Win |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/rachel-brosnahan-wins-golden-globe-best-actress-comedy-marvelous-mrs-maisel-1202652060/ |date=January 8, 2018 |accessdate=January 8, 2018 |journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Perez |first=Lexy |title=Golden Globes: Rachel Brosnahan Wins Best Actress for ''Marvelous Mrs. Maisel'' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/rachel-brosnahan-wins-best-actress-marvelous-mrs-maisel-golden-globes-2018-1071862 |date=January 8, 2018 |accessdate=January 8, 2018 |journal=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Comedy Series]]\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series|Outstanding Performance 